If you know me personally, you&#x2019;ll know I&#x2019;m a big picture thinker, committed to &#x2018;this place&#x2019; - striving to contribute positively here - even in challenging or sensitive circumstances. 

I&#x2019;ve embarked on a new opportunity at ICRIR. Moving from a small organisation back to a large and complex one, working on a differently focused remit, practising and refining another skillset, getting to grips with a new culture. All change. 

At the core of it though - an unwavering commitment to peace and reconciliation remains. 

I may no longer walk into the office via the Garden of Reflection in Derry everyday, but all those reflections are still there. [Along with my love for the many words that adorn the walls] &#x1FA77; 

&#x2018;Further shore is reachable from here.&#x2019; &#x1F4AB;
